https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-substring-without-repeating-characters/description/

*****brute force*****
Generate all substrings starting at each
index and use a set to detect duplicates.
Stop extending when a duplicate is found.

Time  : O(N²)
Space : O(N)

class Solution {
public:
    int lengthOfLongestSubstring(string s) 
    {
        int maxlen=0;
        int n=s.length();

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            unordered_set<char> sett;

            for(int j=i;j<n;j++)
            {
                //break if found in set 
                if(sett.count(s[j])) break;

                //add to set 
                sett.insert(s[j]);

                //update max len 
                maxlen = max(maxlen,j-i+1);
            }
        }
        return maxlen;
    }
};

**********Sliding window***
When duplicate is found,
we throw away all previous work
and start again from i+1.

Can I remove characters from the left
until the duplicate disappears?

Window = substring with unique characters.

Expand right pointer.

If current character becomes duplicate:
    shrink window from left
    until duplicate is removed.

Update maximum window length.

Why while(ump[s[r]] > 1)?
when you add 
ump[s[r]]++;
the only character that can make the window invalid is s[r].
Keep shrinking the window until
the duplicate character s[r]
appears only once.

example:
s = "abba"

Add:
a -> {a:1}

ab -> {a:1,b:1}

abb -> {a:1,b:2}  <-- duplicate b

shrink:
remove a

{a:0,b:2}

still duplicate

remove b

{a:0,b:1}

Time  : O(N)

Space : O(N)

class Solution {
public:
    int lengthOfLongestSubstring(string s) 
    {
        int maxlen=0;
        unordered_map<char,int> ump;
        int l=0,r=0;
        int n=s.length();

        while(r<n)
        {
            //add to map
            ump[s[r]]++;

            //check if exists 
            while(ump[s[r]]>1)
            {
                ump[s[l]]--;
                l++;
            }

            //update max len
            maxlen = max(maxlen,r-l+1);

            r++;
        }
        return maxlen;
    }
};




